identificationRemarks: Nice catch, plethodonlarselli - I wasn't paying attention. I snapped two quick photos before it disappeared into the duff, saw orange on the legs and assumed it was an Ensatina. In hindsight, it didn't move like an Ensatina. It is indeed a torrent salamander, but I'm in southwest Washington, not the Olympic Peninsula, so it must be Columbia Torrent Salamander. I added the second photo - the demarcation line between the brown dorsal and orange ventral ground color can be seen on the tail in that photo - indistinct and straight rather than distinct and wavy, a difference between Columbia and Olympic noted in Amphibians of Washington and Oregon. General Torrent Salamander field marks illustrated in photo include white flecks and lack of dark spots on brown dorsal side of head and body.
